benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid deletion scenarios across varying header and query parameter combinations (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC16, TC18) are covered with 204 responses and appropriate body behavior.
Error handling for invalid inputs and IDs (TC07, TC10, TC15, TC17) is covered, including malformed IDs, invalid customField values, and mixed valid/invalid lists.
Authorization and header edge cases are covered (TC09 for missing header, TC19 for expired/invalid token) in addition to tests that exercise required headers.
Service availability and error responses (TC14) are covered with 503/appropriate error indication.
Non-existent resource handling (TC08) is tested with 404 and error messaging.
Large payload handling (TC12) is covered by deleting 100+ customField IDs and verifying removal.
Header parsing regression scenario (TC20) demonstrates resilience to problematic header formats.
gaps: Concurrency/race condition testing for DELETE on the same resource is not covered.
Caching behavior verification (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses is not covered.
Rate limiting / throttling under burst requests is not covered.
Soft delete semantics (if applicable) are not tested.
Further 5xx error coverage beyond 503 (e.g., 500 Internal Server Error) is not tested.
Explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios (in addition to 401 Unauthorized) are not tested.
recommendations: Add concurrency stress tests to verify behavior when multiple clients delete custom fields for the same invoice item simultaneously.
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on DELETE responses if applicable.
Add rate limiting tests to ensure proper handling under high request throughput.
Include tests to cover soft-delete semantics if the API supports it (e.g., whether deletions are soft or hard).
Extend error handling tests to cover additional 5xx scenarios (besides 503) and explicit 403 Forbidden cases for authorization.
Consider a dedicated test for pagination-like behavior when bulk-deleting very large numbers of IDs, if applicable.
